function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(word[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` higher-order function to create a new array containing only the words that start with a capital letter. The anonymous function `word -> isuppercase(word[1])` checks if the first character of each word is uppercase using the `isuppercase` function. Only words that satisfy this condition are kept in the resulting array.
